In order to study the dermal uptake, time course, and urinary excretion of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons, the concentration of 1-hydroxypyrene in urine was determined by means of high performance liquid chromatography with fluorescence detection before, during, and after the topical treatment with coal tar in 19 patients suffering from prurigo simplex subacuta, microbial eczema, atopic dermatitis, eczematization after scabies, exanthematous lichen ruber, pityriasis lichenoides and cutaneous sarcoidosis.  
